  "summary": "Main\nIn Issue 150 of this publication, we dissected China's coal appetite. This week, we aim to broaden the discussion by looking at India's fossil fuel demand and the associated trends in the coal market. Last year, coal-fired power plants account for approximately 35% of global electricity generation, down from 41% in 2014, reflecting a gradual transition toward cleaner energy sources.",
